DataElement.preferredName: Address Location Unique Record Link Identifier
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A standardized representation of the location of a person, business, building, or organization.:A position, site, or point in space where something can be found._A set of characters used as a code that is unique in the context or the system for which it is created. It serves as a means of identification and reference (often instead of a name) for an entity, person, thing, function, procedure, activity, variable, or body of data.:A sequence of characters used as a linkage between related records._One or more characters used to identify, name, or characterize the nature, properties, or contents of a thing.
